Toy example for C-Fortran interoperability with opaque types

In this example there are no wrappers, at the expense of having to call the
c_loc function in the fortran program (t.f90).

To compile and run:

Fortran example:
  gfortran -c elsi.f90 m_init.f90
  gfortran -o fhh t.f90  elsi.o m_init.o
  ./fhh
         1

C side:

  cc -c test.c
  gfortran -o chh test.o  elsi.o m_init.o  # re-use previous fortran objects
  ./chh
         1
		      